HEADWORD: Spectroscope
<hw>Spec"tro*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Spectrum</ets> + <ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An optical instrument for forming and
examining spectra (as that of solar light, or those produced by flames
in which different substances are volatilized), so as to determine, from
the position of the spectral lines, the composition of the
substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spectroscopical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Spectroscopic</ent>⟦br⟧
